##Special Report | shortage of manpower, forced to resume work, why Wuhan Panel Factory Can Not Stop?

Hey, guys

Function description, here is the "First Finance" magazine (predecessor "first finance weekly") readers club, we discover wonderful business value for you, also invited you to explore the bright business world.

By Sasa and Wang Zhen

In Wuhan, nearly a month in front of the struggle is not only the medical staff, but also chip manufacturing and panel factory employees.

"It's just not going to hold, " Li Ming, a front-line engineer at TCL Huaxing Photoelectric Technology Co. , Ltd. (hereinafter referred to as "Huaxing photoelectric") , told reporters that he has not stopped working since he left the company before the Spring Festival.

Li Ming is at the epicenter of an outbreak of COVID-19 pneumonia in Wuhan. "It's been nearly a month since I've been working twice as hard as usual, " he said. "It may last until March. In addition to being in the worst affected areas and not being able to fully meet their needs for food and supplies, and worrying about infection, many people are really close to their physiological and psychological limits. "

Some employees of Huaxing optronics revealed to the first financial reporter that in order to quickly replace the first-line employees with additional manpower, some departments have already started to take "compulsory" rework measures. If they do not return to work, they will be treated as absenteeism, and will be automatically dismissed if they exceed a certain period of time, this has also led to a strong resistance from some employees.

As of 20:00 on February 15,263 people in Wuhan Huaxing had been found to have fever, cough and other abnormal conditions, and all of them had been sent to hospital for treatment, including 218 people who had been ruled out by hospital diagnosis, according to a huaxing photoelectric circular dated February 15, which was exclusively obtained by China Business News, 45 people were isolated by themselves in the dormitory of the factory area (25 people were isolated by close or indirect contact with fever) . One case was confirmed.

On February 17, the first financial reporter asked Huaxing Guangdian about the resumption of factory work in Wuhan. The company said it had not responded for the time being, saying that previously listed companies had issued announcements on the resumption of work.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
High-intensity operation for nearly a month

According to our reporter's understanding, regardless of whether in Wuhan or not, the main wafer foundry and panel factories are all in normal operation during the Spring Festival period. Several listed companies have announced that they are not affected by the epidemic, and behind these manufacturing factories that keep turning, is the long-term high-intensity operation of front-line staff.

On Feb. 12, TCL's chairman, Li Dongsheng, said in a Weibo Post that due to the special process of the semiconductor display industry, continuous production is required and employees work every day. Under the pressure of the epidemic, TCL Huaxing people in Shenzhen and Wuhan remained on duty to ensure the normal operation of the factories, especially the Wuhan Huaxing Factory, with 7,000 employees under the leadership of the core management. "because Wuhan Huaxing low-temperature polysilicon screens account for 20 per cent of the global supply, the shutdown has had an impact on the global industrial chain. And with the city sealed off, the risk of leaving the site could be even greater. We are working and living in strict accordance with the requirements of prevention and control. We are keeping the plant running normally and there is no outbreak in the plant area."

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Li Dongsheng 12 Feb.

TCL Technology said that from the beginning of 2020 until today (February 11) , Wuhan Huaxing T3 panel production line continued to full production, and in January ahead of schedule to complete the year-old repair, the current production capacity of 50K / month, materials and manpower can meet current production needs, finished product shipping channel normal. From February 1 to February 10,2020, the cumulative T3 casting volume was the same as the same period last year, is expected to continue full production operations in February.

In 2019, Huaxing ranked sixth among global smartphone panel manufacturers, according to Research firm CINNO Research. In a written reply to China Business News on Feb. 17, the agency analyzed that Wuhan, as the center of the new pneumonia outbreak, must be under the greatest pressure on local enterprises to operate and resume work. Because the front section of the panel is as high automation as the semiconductor plant, the manpower demand is not big, and the automation of the module production line in the back section of the panel plant is much less than the front section, the manpower demand is big. It can be seen that Boe and Huaxing optronics have launched temporary job recruitment information, mainly to supplement quality inspection, assembly, storage and other sites staff.

Wang Bin (not his real name) , an employee at Huaxing optronics in Wuhan, confirmed that the remaining employees have been working continuously for at least 20 days since January 22,2008, "under normal circumstances, people on duty during the Spring Festival can take a holiday up to the sixth day of the Lunar New Year, but because people who took a holiday before this year can not return to Wuhan, they can only take it. "

During his stay, Li Ming worked six days a week and took one day off, working regular hours from 8:30 am to 17:30 am and from 8:30 am to 20:30 AM when he was on duty. However, as the current staff is only half the normal state, so the intensity of work is twice normal, "the actual overtime will be until the evening, the average daily work 10-12 hours. "

The main concern is the infection of new pneumonia, in the state of physical and mental fatigue of low immunity, more vulnerable to the virus. "because of the nature of the industry, you need to maintain the equipment in a clean room with constant temperature and humidity, so it's like having all the staff in the same closed air conditioning. Once an employee is infected, the risk of an outbreak is high.". Li Ming said.

In general, clean rooms in the wafer fabrication and panel industries require a higher degree of cleanliness and are safer than the outside world, but if an employee is infected with the virus, the person entering the clean room is itself a virus carrier. What's more, Li Ming points out, the panel industry's front-end process is thinly staffed and risk-free, but the back-end process (module section) is very crowded, "so you could say it's very crowded, so the process doesn't guarantee the efficiency of the clean room. "

Forced return to China stirs controversy

The replacement of long-term left-behind staff is imminent, how to quickly let the staff back to work as quickly as possible has become the key task of the enterprise.

Li Ming said the company advised that workers who took leave years ago would be required to return to work from Feb. 14. If they could not return to work, they would start counting absences and need to make up for them by taking time off or personal leave, otherwise they would be considered absentees.

According to information provided by employees to first financial, some departments have notified employees that they must return to the company by Feb. 18, "If there is any resistance from the local government or if you need assistance in writing a certificate, you can send it back to the company and the company will do everything it can to solve it for everyone, " he said.

However, several employees said that all the notifications with mandatory requirements were sent through wechat groups or over the phone, with no formal document notification. In response, some employees said that the return of the company is not mandatory, but many departments operate in private.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Application form and other materials for returning Chinese employees

Some staff said, Huaxing photoelectric group built inside the "return to work guerrillas" , a person responsible for finishing from all over the Han strategy, sharing easy to release the route.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
While calling employees back to work in Han, some employees said they expect the company to further strengthen the factory epidemic prevention and control measures.

Wang Bin said to the first financial reporter: "The source of infection is not completely closed. ". Also these days began, because Wuhan began to close all the residential areas, so the company let all employees live in dormitories, monitoring body temperature. But from January 22 to February 10, most of the employees took the shuttle bus or drove back and forth, after work in Wuhan contact with WHO, whether contact with the source of infection, it is not controllable, and everyone has to eat the canteen, live in dormitories, take the shuttle bus, and meet together every day."

A video circulating inside the company shows that on Feb. 14, at the dining hall of the T4 complex in Wuhan, during the Dinner Rush, the dining hall was full and there was no effective protective distance. However, images taken at the T3 R & D Cafeteria on the second floor at 5 p.m. on Feb. 17 showed tables with partitions and fewer staff.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The first financial reporter learned that the epidemic prevention management and control measures for returning personnel issued by Huaxing photoelectricity show that the company is stricter in the epidemic prevention and control: After the employees apply for returning to work, they first judge the epidemic area, and then judge the relevant grading management standards for the corresponding epidemic area, reporting to the safety and administration branch for follow-up management. But one employee, Bing He (not his real name) , said that for self-drive back to the company's employees, as long as they can successfully come back, some people apply the day before, the next day they can clock in to work, there is no quarantine.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Classification Standard for returning personnel

Wang said he was surprised: "because it is a wuhan-based enterprise, and most of its employees are from Wuhan and Xiaogan Huanggang in Hubei Province. Some of his colleagues just drive to and fro. Now there are many cases of infection in many residential areas in Wuhan, so the drivers can not be sure that they will not carry the virus. "

Just three days after Li Dongsheng posted on his micro blog, "there is no epidemic in the factory area, " a Feb. 15 China Star report obtained by China Business News reported that as of Feb. 15, at 20:00, a total of 263 people were found to have fever, cough and other abnormal conditions, and all of them were sent to hospital for treatment. Among them, 218 were ruled out by hospital diagnosis, and 45 people were isolated from the dormitory of the factory site by themselves (among them, 25 people were isolated from those who had close or indirect contact with fever) , one confirmed case. Wang said the announcement did not reassure employees.

Staff expectation: More humanistic care

Wuhan is the important town of panel industry in our country. It has gathered five production lines of three big head enterprises: Jingdongfang, TCL Technology and Shentianma.

Panel industry and chip manufacturing industry are the industries with fast growth and broad prospects in China in recent years. Because of the particularity of the industry, Wafer Fabrication Plants and panel factories all year round, usually in the off-season repair and update machine equipment.

On the one hand, if the enterprise is completely shut down, it will bring huge losses to the enterprise and even the Chinese panel industry. Li Ming said the semiconductor industry production line outage will lead to machine accuracy, life, half of the product into scrap, restart the cost of a great deal.

From the enterprise, the production line and equipment of this kind of factory invests huge, often ten billion. If production is stopped, the upfront investment can not be recouped in the short term, and many of the equipment will be idle risk of damage.

Fang Jing, chief analyst of the Electronics Industry at Cinda Securities, pointed out that Huaxing optronics's T4 production line and Boe's B17 production line are currently in the capacity ramp, affected by the epidemic, the ramp speed will be delayed. However, a slowdown in panel factory capacity could exacerbate the shortage of panels.

On the other hand, the safety of employees is being affected. If the outbreak is not properly controlled, it may continue to spread widely. The employees who stayed in the factory for nearly a month also hope to have a chance to breathe.

Wang Bin told reporters that he does not want the company to be particularly affected. The most important two demands are that all employees working from home should be able to work from home. The second is that the company should be able to operate at a minimum capacity. Do not encourage full capacity at this time, too labor-intensive, to reduce the pressure on colleagues in the factory, do not take similar forced way to let colleagues outside the resumption of work.

Li Ming also told China Business News that employees are not unable to understand the company, nor are they resisting working against the company. He just hopes that during the special period, they can pursue less economic interests and show more humane care to their employees."

He did an accounting for the reporter, and the planned cutbacks had limited impact on the company. "The company's current full capacity is 50K per month, which is 50,000 large panels (one is 1.85 m long and 1.55 m wide, and is later cut into 200-300 LCD screens, which are used to calculate capacity in the panel industry) . If February is calculated by half production, monthly production capacity is 30K, then the annual shipment is only 3.33% less, the impact on the entire company's profits is not really big; even if Beijing East, TCL Technology, Shentianma and other domestic leaders all half production in February, the entire industry annual shipment will only be less than 1.5% less, because only involves the Wuhan Company's production capacity, the rest of the domestic cities can normal production.
